# Hardware context: ESP32 DevKitC V4

Board: **ESP32 DevKitC V4**, module **ESP32-WROOM-32D**. Full diagram: `docs/esp32-devkitc-v4-pinout.png`.

## Default buses (typical wiring / ESP-IDF defaults)

| Bus | Role | GPIO |
|-----|------|------|
| UART0 | USB serial debug | TX **1**, RX **3** |
| UART2 | Second UART | TX **17**, RX **16** |
| I2C | SDA / SCL | **21** / **22** |
| SPI (VSPI) | MOSI / MISO / SCK / CS | **23** / **19** / **18** / **5** |
| DAC | DAC1 / DAC2 | **25** / **26** |

## ADC note

With **Wi-Fi on**, **ADC2** GPIOs are unreliable; use **ADC1** (e.g. 32–39; 34–39 are input-only).

## Input-only (no internal pull-up/down)

**34, 35, 36, 39** — use only as inputs (e.g. ADC1).

## Flash / PSRAM strapping — avoid for GPIO

**6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11** — tied to internal flash; do not use as user GPIO.

## Boot / strapping (use with care)

**0, 2, 12, 15** — affect boot mode or flash voltage; OK with correct pull levels at reset.

## Left header (top → bottom)

| Pin label | Notes |
|-----------|--------|
| 3V3, EN, GND, 5V | Power / reset |
| 36 | ADC1_0, input-only |
| 39 | ADC1_3, input-only |
| 34 | ADC1_6, input-only |
| 35 | ADC1_7, input-only |
| 32, 33 | ADC1, touch, 32k crystal pads |
| 25, 26 | ADC2, DAC1/2 |
| 27 | ADC2, touch |
| 14, 12, 13 | ADC2, touch, HSPI (12 strapping) |
| 9–11 | UART1 / flash — **do not use** |
| GND | |

## Right header (top → bottom)

| Pin label | Notes |
|-----------|--------|
| GND | |
| 23, 22, 21 | VSPI MOSI; SCL + RTS0; SDA |
| 1, 3 | UART0 TX/RX (console) |
| GND | |
| 19, 18, 5 | VSPI MISO, CLK, CS |
| 17, 16 | UART2 TX/RX |
| 4, 0, 2, 15 | ADC2, touch; 0/2/15 strapping |
| 8, 7, 6 | Flash — **do not use** |

## Touch (if needed)

Touch0–Touch9 map to GPIO **4, 0, 2, 15, 13, 12, 14, 27, 33, 32** (Touch0 … Touch9).

When suggesting pins for UART to modem, sensors, or LEDs, prefer **UART2 (16/17)** or other free GPIOs, and **never** suggest **6–11** for general I/O.
